1
00:00:55,562 --> 00:00:57,562
[thunder rumbling]

2
00:00:58,229 --> 00:01:00,354
You're working for SherKhan?

3
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,937
SherKhan is working for him,
don't you get it?

4
00:01:05,021 --> 00:01:07,604
I don't work for nobody. I work for us.

5
00:01:07,687 --> 00:01:09,021
Fuck that!

6
00:01:09,104 --> 00:01:13,146
So having me beaten up was
all for us too? Why do you keep lying?

7
00:01:15,312 --> 00:01:18,354
Look at this bullshit!
When are you gonna cut the crap, huh?

8
00:01:18,437 --> 00:01:20,312
Who's Milord? I don't get it.

9
00:01:20,396 --> 00:01:21,562
He's the boss.

10
00:01:22,062 --> 00:01:25,812
He's Fatso's boss.
He had me beaten up, that's who he is.

11
00:01:26,479 --> 00:01:28,229
The biggest dealer in Fort-de-France.

12
00:01:29,187 --> 00:01:31,896
You dealing crack, Kylian?
What are you dealing?

13
00:01:31,979 --> 00:01:33,437
Never crack.

14
00:01:33,521 --> 00:01:35,687
I promise I'd never touch that shit.

15
00:01:38,812 --> 00:01:39,937
Okay.

16
00:01:41,271 --> 00:01:45,687
I know this might be tough to understand,
but it's for our own wellbeing.

17
00:01:45,771 --> 00:01:46,771
All of us.

18
00:01:46,854 --> 00:01:49,771
Crack isn't gonna
keep a roof over our heads.

19
00:01:51,854 --> 00:01:53,896
You dealing? What, weed?

20
00:01:54,812 --> 00:01:57,271
Which block? Fuck's sake, Kylian, explain!

21
00:01:57,354 --> 00:01:59,312
I'm not on the streets.

22
00:02:00,021 --> 00:02:02,604
I dealt a bit of pot
to get enough cash to buy coke.

23
00:02:05,312 --> 00:02:06,687
No one knows who I am.

24
00:02:06,771 --> 00:02:08,521
Trust me, it's safer that way.

25
00:02:08,604 --> 00:02:12,021
I sell the coke where
it earns me the most, in France.

26
00:02:12,937 --> 00:02:15,146
I mean, I will be soon.

27
00:02:15,229 --> 00:02:16,562
I just closed a huge deal.

28
00:02:16,646 --> 00:02:18,854
I got merchandise coming in overseas.

29
00:02:18,937 --> 00:02:20,104
We're talking millions.

30
00:02:21,979 --> 00:02:23,521
Completely insane, this guy.

31
00:02:23,604 --> 00:02:25,104
[phone vibrating]

32
00:02:25,187 --> 00:02:27,937
- [Marvin] We gotta do something.
- [Annabelle] See a therapist?

33
00:02:28,021 --> 00:02:30,146
FATSO - Everything was stolen,
there's nothing left.

34
00:02:30,229 --> 00:02:32,479
[Marvin] I guess it's to be expected
with Mama's death.

35
00:02:32,562 --> 00:02:33,979
He's not coping. We didn't see it.

36
00:02:34,062 --> 00:02:35,979
WE'RE CHANGING HIDEOUTS.
I'LL CALL YOU AFTER.

37
00:02:36,062 --> 00:02:37,062
[Marvin] He's losing it.

38
00:02:41,479 --> 00:02:43,187
It's true, he's Milord.

39
00:02:45,146 --> 00:02:47,146
Milord was Dylan. It connects.

40
00:02:48,562 --> 00:02:53,354
So this son of a bitch swiped
Dylan's username to sell goddamn poison?

41
00:02:54,312 --> 00:02:55,812
That is disgusting.

42
00:02:58,062 --> 00:02:59,562
How long have you been doing this?

43
00:03:02,854 --> 00:03:05,062
Answer her, Milord, or whatever!

44
00:03:06,604 --> 00:03:07,854
Two years, maybe.

45
00:03:09,312 --> 00:03:11,229
Nah, he's being played for sure.

46
00:03:11,312 --> 00:03:14,646
Marv, there's an apartment
full of their shit. It's a huge operation.

47
00:03:15,396 --> 00:03:16,854
Two years.

48
00:03:17,771 --> 00:03:19,187
We were always together in school.

49
00:03:19,979 --> 00:03:21,937
- Had to keep it a secret.
- Stop talking!

50
00:03:30,187 --> 00:03:34,062
Aren't you all fed up, though?
Living in this shack, counting pennies?

51
00:03:34,729 --> 00:03:37,187
Not being able to afford a damn gas stove?

52
00:03:37,771 --> 00:03:40,896
Having to hide the babies
'cause we're too poor for custody?

53
00:03:40,979 --> 00:03:42,604
Who do you think got the damn stove?

54
00:03:43,354 --> 00:03:45,479
How do you think we got the stand back?

55
00:03:45,562 --> 00:03:49,896
It's the best solution to use Milord.
Yeah, it might be hard, but that's life.

56
00:03:52,479 --> 00:03:53,854
You say a shack?

57
00:03:55,521 --> 00:03:57,812
You wouldn't have dared
talk like that in front of Mama.

58
00:04:01,687 --> 00:04:04,646
- Take your things, get out of here.
- Marv--

59
00:04:04,729 --> 00:04:06,354
I said take your shit

60
00:04:06,437 --> 00:04:09,354
and find somewhere else to stay,
'cause you can't stay here.

61
00:04:09,437 --> 00:04:12,604
Better to keep it secret.
It was to keep you out of the mix.

62
00:04:12,687 --> 00:04:16,687
[sucks teeth] Don't give me that bull like
you're a gangster! Life isn't a movie!

63
00:04:17,604 --> 00:04:20,604
You had better knock this shit off.
I mean it. It's pathetic.

64
00:04:23,812 --> 00:04:24,896
Get out.

65
00:04:29,229 --> 00:04:32,229
[bittersweet music playing softly]

66
00:04:35,479 --> 00:04:37,812
Hey! Give me that ring!

67
00:04:37,896 --> 00:04:40,187
Mama thought you were pure, you bastard.

68
00:04:40,271 --> 00:04:41,271
You realize that?

69
00:04:41,354 --> 00:04:43,021
Give it back, now.

70
00:04:46,146 --> 00:04:47,229
No.

71
00:04:51,271 --> 00:04:54,729
[bittersweet music continues playing]

72
00:05:24,687 --> 00:05:26,687
[phone vibrating]

73
00:05:30,479 --> 00:05:33,562
KIKI
I'm sorry

74
00:06:29,521 --> 00:06:32,521
[rap beat playing faintly on headphones]

75
00:06:55,187 --> 00:06:56,812
I DON'T HAVE
THE STRENGTH ANYMORE

76
00:07:16,812 --> 00:07:18,271
[Ambre] Hard to believe, huh?

77
00:07:29,187 --> 00:07:30,271
XHESUS
I miss you already

78
00:07:30,354 --> 00:07:32,812
The weather's nice, I'm thinking of you…
What are you doing?

79
00:07:32,896 --> 00:07:34,729
Why aren't you answering?
Is there a problem?

80
00:07:35,521 --> 00:07:36,937
Why's this guy being a dick?

81
00:08:04,271 --> 00:08:05,562
[sucks teeth]

82
00:08:05,646 --> 00:08:07,604
Fuck this. Shit.

83
00:08:22,854 --> 00:08:24,437
[sighs]

84
00:08:25,771 --> 00:08:27,979
I appreciate it.
It will just be for tonight.

85
00:08:28,062 --> 00:08:29,854
Don't worry, my mom knows.

86
00:08:36,687 --> 00:08:38,646
You get in a fight with your brothers?

87
00:08:40,104 --> 00:08:41,896
It'll blow over. I'm sure it will.

88
00:08:48,062 --> 00:08:49,437
Won't be that simple, I'm afraid.

89
00:08:50,854 --> 00:08:52,771
It will! That's family.

90
00:08:53,354 --> 00:08:54,479
[sighs heavily]

91
00:08:55,146 --> 00:08:56,604
You don't know my family.

92
00:09:04,021 --> 00:09:05,021
Want to drink something?

93
00:09:06,104 --> 00:09:07,229
If you are.

94
00:09:08,812 --> 00:09:11,812
["No Pain No Gain"
by Shaka Zulu & Lylyo playing]

95
00:09:30,771 --> 00:09:33,437
FATSO
Where have you moved to?

96
00:09:43,187 --> 00:09:44,187
Enter.

97
00:09:50,146 --> 00:09:52,146
- [door closes]
- [song stops playing]

98
00:10:01,146 --> 00:10:03,854
I just want to talk with you.

99
00:10:13,771 --> 00:10:15,937
We've just lost our mother.
You know that, I imagine.

100
00:10:22,354 --> 00:10:25,271
I'm worried about Kylian.
He's my responsibility.

101
00:10:26,646 --> 00:10:28,271
He's grieving. He needs structure.

102
00:10:29,562 --> 00:10:31,062
And what he's doing with you here…

103
00:10:31,937 --> 00:10:34,771
this shit is the exact opposite
of what he actually needs right now.

104
00:10:35,521 --> 00:10:39,146
Anyway, all this to say,
you're gonna have to do this without him.

105
00:10:39,229 --> 00:10:40,646
I'm serious, he's done.

106
00:10:42,479 --> 00:10:45,146
- Look, I'm not sure exactly what he said--
- That's not the issue!

107
00:10:45,229 --> 00:10:47,271
I know all about your thing.

108
00:10:47,354 --> 00:10:49,854
And I will not let him
be involved any longer.

109
00:10:50,354 --> 00:10:52,854
All I'm asking is let him be.

110
00:10:54,146 --> 00:10:56,562
Marvin… our business don't work like that.

111
00:10:56,646 --> 00:10:58,062
- [Ludo] Mmm.
- [Marvin] Alexy?

112
00:10:58,812 --> 00:11:01,062
This is happening, you guys hear me?

113
00:11:02,271 --> 00:11:05,937
Look, you're all adults. You know
you can work with anybody you want.

114
00:11:07,812 --> 00:11:10,729
And, anyway, I'm gonna
be on that kid like white on rice.

115
00:11:11,312 --> 00:11:12,896
So there's nothing you can do.

116
00:11:13,396 --> 00:11:15,146
You might want to be careful.

117
00:11:15,229 --> 00:11:16,937
Kylian is 16!

118
00:11:17,021 --> 00:11:20,729
He thinks he's some kinda boss.
He's gonna fall flat on his ass.

119
00:11:21,562 --> 00:11:23,354
He won't go to prison.

120
00:11:23,437 --> 00:11:24,854
But you?

121
00:11:24,937 --> 00:11:26,896
You're all over 18.

122
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:29,187
You realize that?

123
00:11:29,271 --> 00:11:31,771
Do your business without Kylian.

124
00:11:33,771 --> 00:11:36,104
- [door opens]
- You just gonna let him go like that?

125
00:11:36,187 --> 00:11:38,479
- [door closes]
- It's disrespectful, man.

126
00:11:38,562 --> 00:11:39,812
Crazy.

127
00:11:41,354 --> 00:11:42,771
We'll handle it.

128
00:11:44,521 --> 00:11:47,521
[darkly expectant music playing]

129
00:11:53,729 --> 00:11:55,729
[alarm ringing]

130
00:11:59,396 --> 00:12:02,396
- [ringing continues]
- [Lily grunts]

131
00:12:04,187 --> 00:12:05,521
[ringing stops]

132
00:12:07,896 --> 00:12:09,896
[expectant music continues]

133
00:12:17,687 --> 00:12:19,021
[Lily] My uncle's here.

134
00:12:19,604 --> 00:12:20,604
And?

135
00:12:21,312 --> 00:12:24,354
Why does he have to show up at 7:00 a.m.?

136
00:12:24,437 --> 00:12:26,271
He always come this early?

137
00:12:26,354 --> 00:12:27,354
Yeah.

138
00:12:27,937 --> 00:12:31,187
My mother works with him…
for him at city hall.

139
00:12:32,062 --> 00:12:33,062
It's fine.

140
00:12:33,146 --> 00:12:34,146
'Kay.

141
00:12:38,896 --> 00:12:40,604
Are you coming with me to Claire's party?

142
00:12:42,104 --> 00:12:43,187
It's a costume party.

143
00:12:43,271 --> 00:12:45,437
- Got anything white?
- No.

144
00:12:45,521 --> 00:12:46,687
Okay.

145
00:12:46,771 --> 00:12:48,229
I'll just bring you one.

146
00:12:48,312 --> 00:12:50,229
Can dress up as Tony Montana.

147
00:12:50,312 --> 00:12:51,771
I'll be Michelle Pfeiffer.

148
00:12:52,896 --> 00:12:54,146
[laughs]

149
00:12:56,937 --> 00:12:59,062
[woman] Seriously?
You were here yesterday.

150
00:12:59,146 --> 00:13:01,896
[man] Sorry. Yes, but the contractor's
being a pain in the ass.

151
00:13:01,979 --> 00:13:02,979
Really.

152
00:13:03,604 --> 00:13:04,604
Hi.

153
00:13:06,562 --> 00:13:08,646
- Morning.
- [woman] You sleep okay?

154
00:13:08,729 --> 00:13:09,729
[Lily] Yeah, fine.

155
00:13:10,229 --> 00:13:11,437
Same, thanks.

156
00:13:17,354 --> 00:13:20,312
If you can be ready in ten minutes,
I'll drop you off.

157
00:13:20,396 --> 00:13:21,396
[Lily] Okay.

158
00:13:38,354 --> 00:13:39,687
[sighs]

159
00:13:41,812 --> 00:13:43,021
Alex Croquet.

160
00:13:44,521 --> 00:13:46,271
I know. Kylian Lafleur.

161
00:13:47,437 --> 00:13:48,854
I know you too.

162
00:13:50,229 --> 00:13:52,104
Lily has spoken of you.

163
00:13:54,229 --> 00:13:55,687
Your mother just passed.

164
00:13:56,271 --> 00:13:57,521
Tough life.

165
00:14:01,437 --> 00:14:03,437
Go tell your mother I'm heading out.

166
00:14:17,396 --> 00:14:18,562
Lafleur.

167
00:14:21,312 --> 00:14:23,271
Can't say Lily hit the jackpot, huh?

168
00:14:27,437 --> 00:14:28,271
[sighs]

169
00:14:30,521 --> 00:14:31,937
Just how many are in your family?

170
00:14:33,979 --> 00:14:34,812
A lot.

171
00:14:38,687 --> 00:14:39,937
So you've lost count too.

172
00:14:44,396 --> 00:14:47,021
So, to summarize,

173
00:14:48,479 --> 00:14:51,187
you're kicked out
and you're mooching off the Juliards.

174
00:14:51,812 --> 00:14:53,187
What's your plan?

175
00:14:54,979 --> 00:14:57,979
Don't tell me the others
will be showing up here as well.

176
00:15:04,604 --> 00:15:05,604
[sighs]

177
00:15:06,229 --> 00:15:07,729
It's not sustainable.

178
00:15:09,271 --> 00:15:10,271
What?

179
00:15:11,104 --> 00:15:12,604
Your plan.

180
00:15:15,271 --> 00:15:18,146
Your kind's all bloodsuckers.
I see 'em every day.

181
00:15:20,562 --> 00:15:22,604
Not your fault,
you were just brought up that way.

182
00:15:26,062 --> 00:15:27,687
It won't be here, Kylian.

183
00:15:29,562 --> 00:15:30,562
Not my family.

184
00:15:31,646 --> 00:15:33,437
Find yourself another Lily, champ.

185
00:15:37,062 --> 00:15:38,479
Get out of here.

186
00:15:39,312 --> 00:15:40,812
Go steal yourself a bike.

187
00:15:47,396 --> 00:15:48,979
Get your ass out.

188
00:15:50,937 --> 00:15:53,937
[darkly intriguing music playing]

189
00:16:05,521 --> 00:16:08,979
[darkly intriguing music continues]

190
00:16:56,687 --> 00:16:59,271
[faucet running in background]

191
00:17:05,104 --> 00:17:06,896
Oh, hello, Kylian.

192
00:17:06,979 --> 00:17:08,979
- Doing well, Mrs. Torville?
- Oh, yes.

193
00:17:09,062 --> 00:17:10,062
Doing well.

194
00:17:10,687 --> 00:17:12,062
Uh, where's Alexy?

195
00:17:12,146 --> 00:17:13,521
He didn't tell me anything.

196
00:17:13,604 --> 00:17:16,604
Just asked me to come by
to clean the place up a little.

197
00:17:17,146 --> 00:17:18,771
He leave any message for me?

198
00:17:18,854 --> 00:17:20,396
No, I'm afraid not.

199
00:17:21,146 --> 00:17:21,979
Thanks.

200
00:17:28,812 --> 00:17:30,396
[sighs heavily]

201
00:17:33,687 --> 00:17:35,687
[line ringing]

202
00:17:36,604 --> 00:17:37,854
[line disconnects]

203
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:44,062
[line ringing]

204
00:17:45,354 --> 00:17:47,187
[line disconnects]

205
00:18:17,062 --> 00:18:19,187
Mrs. Torville,
may I please borrow your phone?

206
00:18:19,271 --> 00:18:21,187
- Mine is out of battery.
- Here.

207
00:18:23,187 --> 00:18:24,271
Thank you.

208
00:18:29,229 --> 00:18:31,229
[line ringing]

209
00:18:37,187 --> 00:18:39,604
- [Fatso] Yes, Grandma?
- Where are you?

210
00:18:41,271 --> 00:18:43,479
- Forget it.
- You for real?

211
00:18:43,562 --> 00:18:44,562
Very.

212
00:18:45,312 --> 00:18:48,937
Listen up, meet me on the field tomorrow.
You better be there.

213
00:19:08,854 --> 00:19:10,062
You alone?

214
00:19:13,646 --> 00:19:14,646
So what now?

215
00:19:15,521 --> 00:19:18,562
- Where's that tool you borrowed?
- Yo, I promise I don't have it.

216
00:19:19,062 --> 00:19:20,896
- I need it.
- What for?

217
00:19:22,271 --> 00:19:24,021
- You don't have it?
- No.

218
00:19:24,104 --> 00:19:25,229
King threw it away.

219
00:19:26,354 --> 00:19:27,521
Hang on.

220
00:19:35,271 --> 00:19:36,562
What are you doing?

221
00:19:39,562 --> 00:19:41,812
[scoffs] What do you
want me to do with that?

222
00:19:41,896 --> 00:19:44,604
[laughs] Man, I got you! It's real!

223
00:19:54,896 --> 00:19:57,521
That way, I can have it on me
without anyone knowing.

224
00:20:02,021 --> 00:20:03,271
Thanks, my man.

225
00:20:03,354 --> 00:20:05,146
Go pay respects to Mama's grave.

226
00:20:05,729 --> 00:20:06,646
Do I have to?

227
00:20:08,187 --> 00:20:09,062
Yes.

228
00:20:16,771 --> 00:20:17,937
Will you tell Milord?

229
00:20:21,729 --> 00:20:24,979
- What?
- Will you tell Milord I helped out?

230
00:20:29,437 --> 00:20:30,521
Yeah, I'll tell him.

231
00:20:35,062 --> 00:20:38,521
- [man 1] Yo, pour me another shot.
- [man 2] You're gonna drain the bottle.

232
00:20:38,604 --> 00:20:41,604
[indistinct chatter
continues in background]

233
00:20:43,229 --> 00:20:44,979
Thought I asked you to watch the bar.

234
00:20:45,062 --> 00:20:47,521
Well, I'm watching someone else
while you're here.

235
00:20:48,021 --> 00:20:51,396
- You in love or what?
- [sucks teeth] I'm pissed off at this man.

236
00:20:52,187 --> 00:20:54,187
He better be ready if I see him.

237
00:20:54,729 --> 00:20:58,104
And you in love with SherKhan or what?
Why are you eyeballing him?

238
00:20:59,396 --> 00:21:02,187
Remember that bastard
returned our cash to SherKhan?

239
00:21:03,271 --> 00:21:05,812
You forget all the risks
you took for that money?

240
00:21:07,187 --> 00:21:08,979
Of course I haven't forgotten.

241
00:21:09,687 --> 00:21:11,479
Well, we're getting it back.

242
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:15,271
It's ours.
Just gotta find out where it's hidden.

243
00:21:21,854 --> 00:21:22,979
Follow the next guy.

244
00:21:23,062 --> 00:21:25,896
- [Annabelle] Yeah, okay.
- [suspenseful music playing]

245
00:21:45,021 --> 00:21:48,021
[suspenseful music continues]

246
00:21:51,229 --> 00:21:53,229
[men chatting indistinctly]

247
00:22:01,229 --> 00:22:03,521
[engine sputters and dies]

248
00:22:07,146 --> 00:22:08,146
[horn honks]

249
00:22:08,229 --> 00:22:10,146
[engine sputtering]

250
00:22:16,187 --> 00:22:19,021
[suspenseful music continues]

251
00:22:27,771 --> 00:22:28,646
Hello.

252
00:22:28,729 --> 00:22:29,979
[women] Hello.

253
00:22:42,937 --> 00:22:44,771
I thought I saw
your ugly-ass face, Lafleur.

254
00:22:44,854 --> 00:22:46,646
- What you want?
- The fuck you care?

255
00:22:46,729 --> 00:22:49,854
- You following me?
- You think you're a star, is that it?

256
00:22:49,937 --> 00:22:50,937
Doing my nails.

257
00:22:55,812 --> 00:22:56,812
I'll wait outside.

258
00:22:56,896 --> 00:22:58,187
If you want.

259
00:23:00,812 --> 00:23:02,271
Okay, what do you want?

260
00:23:03,562 --> 00:23:04,646
Cheapest.

261
00:23:04,729 --> 00:23:07,354
Basic manicure, five euros.

262
00:23:07,437 --> 00:23:08,437
Perfect!

263
00:23:16,062 --> 00:23:17,229
[sucks teeth]

264
00:23:21,562 --> 00:23:24,479
Your little buddies'll love this.
See ya, homo.

265
00:23:28,146 --> 00:23:29,729
I don't care. Go on.

266
00:23:29,812 --> 00:23:32,062
["Madame" by X-Man playing]

267
00:23:35,854 --> 00:23:37,104
That's not bad.

268
00:23:38,271 --> 00:23:40,729
I like guys
who take pride in their appearance.

269
00:23:42,937 --> 00:23:45,812
Well, what do you want from me now?

270
00:23:46,687 --> 00:23:50,812
It's a shame what happened the other day.
Didn't get to know each other.

271
00:23:52,062 --> 00:23:53,521
Nicely put.

272
00:23:54,687 --> 00:23:56,104
What do you want?

273
00:23:56,187 --> 00:23:57,771
Just a little spying.

274
00:23:58,562 --> 00:23:59,646
On who?

275
00:24:00,146 --> 00:24:02,937
SherKhan's crew. They know me.

276
00:24:03,021 --> 00:24:04,062
SherKhan again?

277
00:24:04,771 --> 00:24:07,312
- You're obsessed!
- I'll give you five grand.

278
00:24:11,396 --> 00:24:13,104
Plus 50% of what you make.

279
00:24:13,187 --> 00:24:15,187
- What?
- We're partners, aren't we?

280
00:24:15,271 --> 00:24:16,604
50/50.

281
00:24:16,687 --> 00:24:17,854
[SherKhan] Yo, Lafleur!

282
00:24:24,896 --> 00:24:29,854
So, what, not fleeing for the hills?
You lose that lame little scooter?

283
00:24:29,937 --> 00:24:32,646
I like men who clean up nice,
but not little bitches.

284
00:24:34,396 --> 00:24:35,562
Your guy works for free.

285
00:24:35,646 --> 00:24:38,521
He sold my shit in France
without taking commission.

286
00:24:38,604 --> 00:24:39,604
Let's do it again.

287
00:24:39,687 --> 00:24:40,812
[woman] Jérôme!

288
00:24:42,271 --> 00:24:43,646
You gonna be a King?

289
00:24:45,146 --> 00:24:47,687
Yo, if you're looking for a real G,
call up your boy, SherKhan.

290
00:24:53,479 --> 00:24:54,771
[woman] Jérôme!

291
00:24:55,687 --> 00:24:56,771
Come on.

292
00:25:00,604 --> 00:25:01,604
Your mom is calling.

293
00:25:02,396 --> 00:25:03,937
[woman] Let's go, Jérôme!

294
00:25:09,021 --> 00:25:10,437
You want to know me?

295
00:25:11,979 --> 00:25:14,979
[suspenseful music playing]

296
00:25:56,437 --> 00:25:58,812
I like your guys. Punctual.

297
00:26:02,646 --> 00:26:03,646
Where are you hiding it?

298
00:26:04,562 --> 00:26:05,562
In your ass.

299
00:26:07,146 --> 00:26:08,479
Original.

300
00:26:10,729 --> 00:26:13,479
The point of using groceries
is not to hide them.

301
00:26:15,437 --> 00:26:17,937
Keeping up appearances, that's all.

302
00:26:20,812 --> 00:26:24,437
When the tide is low,
you'll all see little crabs and shrimps

303
00:26:24,521 --> 00:26:25,646
hide under the sand.

304
00:26:26,437 --> 00:26:29,604
They typically come out at night to eat.
Almost always at night.

305
00:26:30,646 --> 00:26:33,646
Okay, does anyone
have any questions about this?

306
00:26:33,729 --> 00:26:35,812
- [kids] No!
- [teacher] Hmm.

307
00:26:35,896 --> 00:26:37,854
- Are you hungry?
- [kids] Yes!

308
00:26:37,937 --> 00:26:39,146
All right, let's go.

309
00:26:39,229 --> 00:26:40,896
[indistinct chatter and laughter]

310
00:26:47,104 --> 00:26:49,437
Excuse me? So sorry,
but I can't stay any longer.

311
00:26:49,521 --> 00:26:51,854
- I was only free until noon.
- Oh, yes, yes, no problem.

312
00:26:51,937 --> 00:26:53,312
I appreciate you helping us out.

313
00:26:53,396 --> 00:26:54,812
Thanks.

314
00:26:59,771 --> 00:27:00,604
Thaïs!

315
00:27:01,771 --> 00:27:03,354
- I'm going.
- See ya!

316
00:27:06,896 --> 00:27:08,896
- [kids laughing]
- [indistinct chatter]

317
00:27:09,854 --> 00:27:11,354
[unsettling music playing]

318
00:27:13,687 --> 00:27:14,687
Nolan?

319
00:27:21,687 --> 00:27:23,646
- Who's that man?
- Uncle Jocelyn.

320
00:27:23,729 --> 00:27:25,104
Uncle Jocelyn?

321
00:27:26,146 --> 00:27:27,146
Hey, Jocelyn!

322
00:27:28,396 --> 00:27:30,271
Jocelyn! Yo!

323
00:27:30,354 --> 00:27:32,354
[dramatic music building slowly]

324
00:27:33,604 --> 00:27:35,646
What the hell is he doing here?

325
00:27:40,604 --> 00:27:43,604
[dramatic music playing]

326
00:28:04,021 --> 00:28:06,187
- What you doin' here?
- Mind your own shit, Milord!

327
00:28:12,812 --> 00:28:13,646
Get out!

328
00:28:25,521 --> 00:28:26,896
You're fucking me over.

329
00:28:26,979 --> 00:28:30,646
You're out here rambling
about how the streets will save us.

330
00:28:30,729 --> 00:28:31,896
All your bullshit.

331
00:28:31,979 --> 00:28:33,937
And you blow it all up, man.

332
00:28:34,812 --> 00:28:35,812
What for?

333
00:28:36,312 --> 00:28:38,396
- Mad you're not the man of the house?
- [chuckles]

334
00:28:38,479 --> 00:28:41,146
While you're making ten kilos,
I'm making over 80.

335
00:28:42,104 --> 00:28:43,687
I buy all my shit.

336
00:28:43,771 --> 00:28:44,771
I don't steal it.

337
00:28:45,354 --> 00:28:47,312
Put it on your CV, if you want a job.

338
00:28:48,271 --> 00:28:50,687
My team dropped me 'cause of you.

339
00:28:50,771 --> 00:28:53,937
I'm in real fucking deep shit now
thanks to you.

340
00:28:54,896 --> 00:28:56,354
I want you to talk to them with me.

341
00:28:56,437 --> 00:28:58,937
- Yeah? For what?
- Tell them that you're an idiot.

342
00:28:59,021 --> 00:29:01,021
And that you're never
gonna cause problems again.

343
00:29:01,104 --> 00:29:03,104
[laughing]

344
00:29:03,187 --> 00:29:06,479
Man, I gotta hand it to you.
You got real nerve, man.

345
00:29:07,604 --> 00:29:10,104
No one can hold a candle to you.
Respect, man.

346
00:29:10,187 --> 00:29:11,687
That's a fact.

347
00:29:12,479 --> 00:29:13,479
Ah…

348
00:29:14,062 --> 00:29:17,146
So why haven't I busted your teeth? Hmm?

349
00:29:17,229 --> 00:29:19,646
I guess I'm too kind.
Should've done it a long time ago.

350
00:29:19,729 --> 00:29:23,187
Should've yanked one out every time
you said something I didn't like.

351
00:29:23,271 --> 00:29:25,021
You'd be eating mashed potatoes.

352
00:29:25,771 --> 00:29:26,854
So get out of here.

353
00:29:28,604 --> 00:29:29,604
Yo!

354
00:29:35,896 --> 00:29:38,021
[yelling] You son of a bitch
piece of shit!

355
00:29:38,104 --> 00:29:39,896
What did you do with Dad?

356
00:29:39,979 --> 00:29:41,771
He's sending Jocelyn to monitor the kids?

357
00:29:41,854 --> 00:29:43,979
- [Kylian] Stop!
- What the fuck did you do?

358
00:29:44,062 --> 00:29:46,396
You dealing with Dad? Goddamn bastard!

359
00:29:46,979 --> 00:29:49,437
- [Kylian] Stop it!
- We agreed to not get them involved, yeah?

360
00:29:49,521 --> 00:29:52,729
That'd we'd keep them out!
You really are a bunch of assholes.

361
00:29:52,812 --> 00:29:54,771
You, Dad, and yeah, bro, you too!

362
00:29:55,354 --> 00:29:57,687
I swear to you,
next time he gets anywhere close to them,

363
00:29:57,771 --> 00:29:59,562
I'll goddamn destroy you!

364
00:30:03,146 --> 00:30:04,479
[Kingsley whistles]

365
00:30:04,562 --> 00:30:07,229
You're just winning hearts left and right.

366
00:30:07,312 --> 00:30:08,854
Mmm-mmm.

367
00:30:13,479 --> 00:30:14,479
Come here.

368
00:30:15,396 --> 00:30:16,937
Did Milord tell you?

369
00:30:17,562 --> 00:30:19,604
Yeah. He wants to test you.

370
00:30:19,687 --> 00:30:20,729
That's dope!

371
00:30:20,812 --> 00:30:22,354
What are we doing here?

372
00:30:22,437 --> 00:30:23,437
Scaring someone.

373
00:30:23,937 --> 00:30:24,854
Who?

374
00:30:25,354 --> 00:30:27,354
[indistinct chatter]

375
00:30:29,312 --> 00:30:31,312
[indistinct chatter continues]

376
00:30:34,229 --> 00:30:36,396
- Oh, that's Uncle Jocelyn!
- Shh!

377
00:30:37,021 --> 00:30:38,604
[man] Damn straight we are.

378
00:30:38,687 --> 00:30:40,396
[Jocelyn] I gotta take a piss.

379
00:30:45,104 --> 00:30:46,437
[man] Watch out.

380
00:30:48,854 --> 00:30:50,854
[urinating]

381
00:30:52,604 --> 00:30:53,646
[gasps]

382
00:30:55,396 --> 00:30:57,229
Man, don't you ever come near the family.

383
00:30:57,312 --> 00:30:58,187
Got it?

384
00:30:58,271 --> 00:31:00,396
You ever get within
a single block of the kids,

385
00:31:00,479 --> 00:31:03,021
- I swear no one will ever find your body.
- [groans]

386
00:31:03,521 --> 00:31:06,437
- Understood? Don't come near the family.
- [dull thud]

387
00:31:06,521 --> 00:31:09,146
- [groaning]
- [Léo grunts]

388
00:31:09,729 --> 00:31:12,646
- [blows landing]
- [Jocelyn groaning]

389
00:31:14,437 --> 00:31:15,437
Enough.

390
00:31:17,229 --> 00:31:18,271
[Jocelyn coughs]

391
00:31:20,021 --> 00:31:21,896
And tell Dad the deal's the same.

392
00:31:22,396 --> 00:31:23,687
Five percent. That's it.

393
00:31:24,604 --> 00:31:26,521
We don't give in to threats.

394
00:31:29,979 --> 00:31:31,729
- [grunting]
- Ahh!

395
00:31:31,812 --> 00:31:32,979
I said enough!

396
00:31:35,437 --> 00:31:37,604
- [coughing]
- [Kylian] Let's go.

397
00:31:41,146 --> 00:31:42,604
Did I do well?

398
00:31:47,354 --> 00:31:48,521
Give me the gun.

399
00:31:54,437 --> 00:31:57,062
- [woman] Yes, we've made a note.
- [door chimes]

400
00:31:57,146 --> 00:31:59,146
[indistinct chatter]

401
00:32:06,021 --> 00:32:08,021
[indistinct chatter continues]

402
00:32:13,646 --> 00:32:15,396
Put this on twice a day.

403
00:32:15,479 --> 00:32:19,354
After, use it as a mask on your face
and keep it damp.

404
00:32:21,437 --> 00:32:24,312
- Then you rinse it off and apply ointment.
- [grunts]

405
00:32:28,479 --> 00:32:30,312
You got a real good heart.

406
00:32:30,396 --> 00:32:33,104
Hope they pay you well at this hospital.

407
00:32:33,771 --> 00:32:34,896
It's fine.

408
00:32:36,979 --> 00:32:38,896
Not afraid they'll return?

409
00:32:39,646 --> 00:32:40,646
Who?

410
00:32:41,354 --> 00:32:42,479
The guys who did this.

411
00:32:42,562 --> 00:32:43,604
[sucks teeth]

412
00:32:44,229 --> 00:32:47,896
[grunts] Bunch of losers.
They can't scare me.

413
00:32:50,312 --> 00:32:51,521
[Cassandra] Then who?

414
00:32:53,854 --> 00:32:54,937
Just drop it.

415
00:33:00,312 --> 00:33:01,646
You know who my cousin is?

416
00:33:04,354 --> 00:33:05,937
You know SherKhan?

417
00:33:08,187 --> 00:33:09,521
When I'm out of here…

418
00:33:10,896 --> 00:33:11,896
What?

419
00:33:12,896 --> 00:33:15,729
It won't be a "welcome home" party,
that's for damn sure.

420
00:33:16,479 --> 00:33:18,979
So don't make me better too fast.
[chuckling]

421
00:33:21,271 --> 00:33:24,229
You know, I do spells too, if you like.

422
00:33:25,187 --> 00:33:28,479
- Yeah? You can for real?
- [darkly introspective music playing]

423
00:33:30,271 --> 00:33:33,354
Like… would he know it's from me?

424
00:33:35,396 --> 00:33:37,604
But it won't be anything too extreme?

425
00:33:37,687 --> 00:33:39,229
Doesn't have to be.

426
00:33:39,312 --> 00:33:40,521
Okay.

427
00:33:41,062 --> 00:33:45,396
- Don't spells need hair and shit?
- I just need a sense of his habits.

428
00:33:45,479 --> 00:33:47,021
Learn about him more.

429
00:33:47,687 --> 00:33:50,396
I need to get a visual idea
of where he goes.

430
00:33:52,771 --> 00:33:55,229
Well, he's got his bar in Trénelle.

431
00:33:55,812 --> 00:33:57,521
And he visits his mother.

432
00:33:58,021 --> 00:34:01,729
He often hangs out at the Marina du Marin,
that asshole.

433
00:34:01,812 --> 00:34:04,021
That's where his dope is shipped from.

434
00:34:05,729 --> 00:34:08,104
[Kingsley] Hold up.
SherKhan is using Croquet's boat?

435
00:34:08,187 --> 00:34:09,354
No.

436
00:34:09,437 --> 00:34:10,479
Yep.

437
00:34:12,146 --> 00:34:13,854
Man, amazing.

438
00:34:13,937 --> 00:34:15,729
You made him talk! How'd you do it?

439
00:34:15,812 --> 00:34:17,021
I'm a professional.

440
00:34:17,104 --> 00:34:18,229
[Thaïs] One euro each.

441
00:34:18,312 --> 00:34:19,562
[woman] All right.

442
00:34:22,354 --> 00:34:25,396
[Kingsley] Thaïs, Mathis, Nolan!
Let's go home.

443
00:34:25,479 --> 00:34:27,312
We haven't finished!

444
00:34:27,979 --> 00:34:32,229
Seems to me that pretty soon
they won't have to work the stand.

445
00:34:32,812 --> 00:34:36,271
Damn straight, darling!
Our life is about to change!

446
00:34:37,604 --> 00:34:40,979
[pensive music playing]

447
00:35:30,437 --> 00:35:33,062
[pensive music continues]

448
00:36:00,896 --> 00:36:03,312
[bag crinkling]

449
00:36:24,354 --> 00:36:25,812
Eighty kilos on the way.

450
00:36:26,396 --> 00:36:27,396
One million euros.

451
00:36:29,062 --> 00:36:31,312
- I know.
- So what are you doing, then?

452
00:36:32,437 --> 00:36:34,271
Couldn't be sure
your other phones were safe.

453
00:36:35,104 --> 00:36:36,104
King took them.

454
00:36:36,187 --> 00:36:38,187
Don't feed me bullshit. Not one message.

455
00:36:38,271 --> 00:36:40,062
You cut me out completely.
What's happening?

456
00:36:40,979 --> 00:36:42,396
Your brother came to see us.

457
00:36:44,187 --> 00:36:45,104
Marvin.

458
00:36:46,979 --> 00:36:48,979
We can't deal with this bullshit.

459
00:36:49,062 --> 00:36:52,187
Your brother turns up, stirring up shit.
The other making trouble? Not cool.

460
00:36:53,187 --> 00:36:54,979
[Peace] You gotta rein them in.

461
00:36:55,062 --> 00:36:58,146
They don't respect you,
so they don't respect any of us.

462
00:37:00,271 --> 00:37:01,604
This shit's fucked.

463
00:37:01,687 --> 00:37:02,729
I won't lie to you.

464
00:37:02,812 --> 00:37:04,812
I don't know what to tell my new buyers.

465
00:37:04,896 --> 00:37:07,021
- Meaning?
- Guys from Grenoble.

466
00:37:07,104 --> 00:37:09,896
They're solid.
They pick their coworkers carefully.

467
00:37:09,979 --> 00:37:12,812
We don't know if you're with us or not.
That'll piss them off.

468
00:37:14,437 --> 00:37:15,979
What are you planning on telling 'em?

469
00:37:17,979 --> 00:37:19,896
If they ask me, I don't know, man.

470
00:37:23,937 --> 00:37:25,354
Marvin, what'd he tell you?

471
00:37:26,271 --> 00:37:27,812
[sighs] To do it without you.

472
00:37:27,896 --> 00:37:29,062
[laughs]

473
00:37:35,479 --> 00:37:36,896
You're gonna go ahead without me?

474
00:37:37,854 --> 00:37:40,562
With everything going on,
not sure if we're gonna do any of it.

475
00:37:41,271 --> 00:37:43,479
- This shit is messy.
- I got it.

476
00:37:44,062 --> 00:37:44,979
No, you don't.

477
00:37:45,771 --> 00:37:47,687
What's that? Must've misheard you.

478
00:37:48,729 --> 00:37:51,437
[menacingly] You don't got shit.

479
00:37:53,396 --> 00:37:54,437
[exhales]

480
00:37:55,896 --> 00:37:59,562
[darkly intriguing music playing]

481
00:38:06,562 --> 00:38:08,229
We got two choices.

482
00:38:09,062 --> 00:38:10,396
Either we go to war…

483
00:38:13,229 --> 00:38:14,729
or we get fuckin' rich.

484
00:38:22,146 --> 00:38:24,312
[Pearl] And how
are you gonna deal with him?

485
00:38:29,937 --> 00:38:31,812
Can you send me a recent resume?

486
00:38:31,896 --> 00:38:32,937
Mmm-hmm.

487
00:38:33,854 --> 00:38:36,187
What about your time gardening
at the Balata?

488
00:38:36,271 --> 00:38:38,021
I was only there two months.

489
00:38:38,104 --> 00:38:39,896
[woman] So what? Put it.

490
00:38:41,854 --> 00:38:44,104
You gotta work on your cover letter, too.

491
00:38:44,187 --> 00:38:45,312
[Marvin sighs]

492
00:38:47,521 --> 00:38:48,521
I'm tired.

493
00:38:49,021 --> 00:38:50,062
I know.

494
00:38:51,646 --> 00:38:55,896
SOS GARDENING
THE FIRST UBER FOR GARDENING

495
00:39:06,229 --> 00:39:08,396
It's been a shitstorm ever since Mama.

496
00:39:08,896 --> 00:39:12,479
We've got nothing to bind us.
She held us together.

497
00:39:13,937 --> 00:39:15,562
No way we're gonna make it.

498
00:39:16,146 --> 00:39:17,812
No, none of that's true.

499
00:39:18,396 --> 00:39:20,896
We're gonna grow distant
or kill each other.

500
00:39:22,562 --> 00:39:25,646
This, it's all just a rough patch.

501
00:39:25,729 --> 00:39:27,271
I know you guys.

502
00:39:27,354 --> 00:39:28,604
You're strong.

503
00:39:28,687 --> 00:39:30,396
You'll all be okay.

504
00:39:31,021 --> 00:39:33,729
You handled Kylian just as you should.

505
00:39:33,812 --> 00:39:35,437
Did what you had to do.

506
00:39:35,521 --> 00:39:37,604
That took some big balls.

507
00:39:38,354 --> 00:39:41,021
Like… a lot?

508
00:39:41,104 --> 00:39:42,312
More than two?

509
00:39:42,396 --> 00:39:44,396
[both laughing]

510
00:39:47,271 --> 00:39:48,979
[loud knocking on door]

511
00:39:50,812 --> 00:39:52,646
- Expecting someone?
- Mmm-mmm.

512
00:40:00,229 --> 00:40:01,521
Let us in.

513
00:40:29,229 --> 00:40:30,854
What are you doing with Kylian?

514
00:40:30,937 --> 00:40:33,229
Why the fuck you here?
Why the fuck are any of you here?

515
00:40:33,312 --> 00:40:36,021
Seems we got an issue with you.

516
00:40:36,604 --> 00:40:38,771
I've been told
you were stirring up some shit.

517
00:40:38,854 --> 00:40:40,104
Came to see for myself.

518
00:40:40,979 --> 00:40:42,187
You're talking to me?

519
00:40:45,771 --> 00:40:47,021
[scoffs]

520
00:40:56,979 --> 00:40:58,021
Get the fuck out.

521
00:40:59,146 --> 00:41:00,646
Had no business talkin' to Fatso.

522
00:41:01,354 --> 00:41:03,437
It's fine. We're moving, anyway.

523
00:41:04,396 --> 00:41:07,479
But let's make a few things clear.
Don't ever come back.

524
00:41:07,562 --> 00:41:10,396
Forget about them.
Keep out of my shit. Shut your mouth.

525
00:41:11,104 --> 00:41:12,146
You got it?

526
00:41:13,187 --> 00:41:16,271
- [sucks teeth] Get the fuck out my home!
- [pan sizzling]

527
00:41:19,437 --> 00:41:20,604
[Marvin] Hmm.

528
00:41:25,187 --> 00:41:26,021
Uh-uh.

529
00:41:26,521 --> 00:41:28,396
Have a bite, man. Sit down.

530
00:41:40,479 --> 00:41:42,062
You're gonna piss them off, you know.

531
00:42:00,187 --> 00:42:01,271
You're out of your minds.

532
00:42:02,812 --> 00:42:03,729
Yup.

533
00:42:04,229 --> 00:42:05,854
That's why we need a guarantee.

534
00:42:13,854 --> 00:42:15,479
- Marvin.
- Hang on.

535
00:42:15,562 --> 00:42:17,937
"Hang on"? What are you doing, Kylian?

536
00:42:18,021 --> 00:42:19,146
What's happening?

537
00:42:19,229 --> 00:42:21,146
This is just family business.

538
00:42:21,229 --> 00:42:23,562
- Let us deal with it, yeah?
- What? You're in my house!

539
00:42:23,646 --> 00:42:26,312
- [Marvin] Chloé, please stop. Enough.
- Hell no, I won't stop.

540
00:42:28,896 --> 00:42:32,646
Stuffing your face with my food?
I don't give a fuck.

541
00:42:34,146 --> 00:42:35,146
Kylian…

542
00:42:35,854 --> 00:42:39,937
keep up this act all you want,
but not with me.

543
00:42:40,021 --> 00:42:42,479
Could have a sleepover here too.

544
00:42:44,062 --> 00:42:46,729
Want to piss me off that badly?
In my house?

545
00:42:47,771 --> 00:42:50,521
Do you know what it means
to show up at a safehouse?

546
00:42:50,604 --> 00:42:52,979
Means you're a dead man walking.

547
00:42:53,521 --> 00:42:55,146
Means we'll rearrange your face

548
00:42:55,229 --> 00:42:58,062
till your little girlfriend
can't recognize you anymore.

549
00:42:58,937 --> 00:43:00,562
Brother or not, changes nothing.

550
00:43:00,646 --> 00:43:02,729
Don't pull that shit ever again, Marvin.

551
00:43:02,812 --> 00:43:06,187
Understand me? There are rules
and they go beyond you and I.

552
00:43:06,271 --> 00:43:09,396
So you better swear to me
that you won't be a problem.

553
00:43:11,937 --> 00:43:13,062
Swear.

554
00:43:14,396 --> 00:43:16,146
Say it, Marvin. Who cares?

555
00:43:17,896 --> 00:43:19,479
[sighs] Okay.

556
00:43:21,146 --> 00:43:24,562
Do you swear that there'll
never be any more problems?

557
00:43:27,687 --> 00:43:29,187
I swear. Now beat it.

558
00:43:30,062 --> 00:43:32,354
[gentle music playing]

559
00:43:32,437 --> 00:43:33,854
Thank you.

560
00:43:37,062 --> 00:43:40,104
[gentle music continues]

561
00:43:58,104 --> 00:44:01,104
- [rap beat playing on headphones]
- [rapping indistinctly]

562
00:44:13,104 --> 00:44:15,312
[woman] Ambre? Ambre!

563
00:44:15,396 --> 00:44:17,687
[shouting] Ambre! Clean this now.

564
00:44:18,854 --> 00:44:21,062
[rap beat continues playing]

565
00:44:21,146 --> 00:44:23,937
[in French] ♪ Workin' hard, money's tight
No matter how hard we try ♪

566
00:44:24,021 --> 00:44:27,104
♪ They're waiting for your decline
Show's over 'cause we ain't got a dime ♪

567
00:44:27,187 --> 00:44:30,229
♪ Don't give a fuck what you think
I won't waste my time ♪

568
00:44:30,312 --> 00:44:32,312
♪ Been feelin' dead inside
Since she passed ♪

569
00:44:32,396 --> 00:44:33,729
♪ Got my heart feeling tight ♪

570
00:44:33,812 --> 00:44:36,562
♪ Sandmen, slumlords
I'm wipin' them out just the same ♪

571
00:44:36,646 --> 00:44:39,521
♪ Fuck this shitty life
These rhymes are my escape ♪

572
00:44:39,604 --> 00:44:42,979
♪ I want to succeed
I want to work hard and touch the sky ♪

573
00:44:43,062 --> 00:44:46,271
♪ Sandmen, slumlords
I'm wipin' them out just the same… ♪

574
00:44:46,354 --> 00:44:49,021
- [rap continues in background]
- [man in English] Hey!

575
00:44:49,646 --> 00:44:51,854
[partygoer] Hey! Whoo!

576
00:44:51,937 --> 00:44:54,937
[Ambre rapping continues in background]

577
00:45:13,104 --> 00:45:15,104
[rap beat fading]

578
00:45:22,062 --> 00:45:23,646
Why'd you bring me here?

579
00:45:24,854 --> 00:45:28,312
Got no place to go.
Not welcome at the house anymore.

580
00:45:30,562 --> 00:45:32,187
Wasn't my decision.

581
00:45:33,812 --> 00:45:34,812
Sure.

582
00:45:35,646 --> 00:45:36,812
Never mind.

583
00:45:39,604 --> 00:45:42,437
I'm better off among the dead
than among the living.

584
00:45:59,312 --> 00:46:00,521
[Annabelle] What's that?

585
00:46:01,521 --> 00:46:02,937
[Kylian] It's my shipment.

586
00:46:05,396 --> 00:46:07,312
- How much?
- Taping me?

587
00:46:07,396 --> 00:46:09,771
Are you serious? Come on!

588
00:46:09,854 --> 00:46:11,021
[chuckles] I'm kidding.

589
00:46:13,979 --> 00:46:15,396
Why did you ask me here?

590
00:46:15,896 --> 00:46:19,146
I'll tell you.
But first, I gotta ask you something.

591
00:46:20,646 --> 00:46:23,562
If Marvin and King find out I'm with you,
I'm a dead woman.

592
00:46:24,562 --> 00:46:26,021
Last time, how much did you make?

593
00:46:27,646 --> 00:46:28,771
Four hundred.

594
00:46:29,271 --> 00:46:30,646
How many kilos?

595
00:46:30,729 --> 00:46:31,771
Twenty.

596
00:46:33,437 --> 00:46:34,646
We got eighty.

597
00:46:36,729 --> 00:46:40,437
I got guys in Grenoble who are buying,
but I might have an issue with them.

598
00:46:40,937 --> 00:46:41,854
Why's that?

599
00:46:42,354 --> 00:46:45,646
One of my guys set it all up,
but now I got some problems.

600
00:46:45,729 --> 00:46:47,354
He's not trustworthy.

601
00:46:52,104 --> 00:46:54,021
- The guy you worked with--
- Xhésus.

602
00:46:54,104 --> 00:46:55,187
Xhésus.

603
00:46:55,979 --> 00:46:57,521
You want his digits.

604
00:46:57,604 --> 00:46:58,521
Yeah.

605
00:47:00,854 --> 00:47:03,187
You're still gonna
need someone over there to receive it.

606
00:47:03,271 --> 00:47:04,979
Fatso will be there.

607
00:47:05,062 --> 00:47:06,187
Let me do it.

608
00:47:06,271 --> 00:47:07,521
What? No.

609
00:47:09,479 --> 00:47:10,771
No Xhésus, then.

610
00:47:17,062 --> 00:47:19,146
- All right, I'm off.
- Hang on.

611
00:47:19,646 --> 00:47:20,771
What?

612
00:47:26,062 --> 00:47:27,312
Belle?

613
00:47:28,646 --> 00:47:30,687
- Why is she here?
- Xhésus is her contact.

614
00:47:30,771 --> 00:47:32,562
- What?
- So she's going with you.

615
00:47:33,646 --> 00:47:35,604
Hell no. You better be joking.

616
00:47:36,396 --> 00:47:38,354
You brought this on yourself, man.

617
00:47:38,854 --> 00:47:41,937
You, Peace, K2R,
you forced me to go after my brother.

618
00:47:42,562 --> 00:47:43,771
So this is revenge?

619
00:47:43,854 --> 00:47:45,229
I make changes accordingly.

620
00:47:47,562 --> 00:47:50,687
So we were wrong about your brother?
Should've ignored him?

621
00:47:50,771 --> 00:47:54,479
No, of course not, but all you had to do
was tell me that my brother talked to you.

622
00:47:54,562 --> 00:47:56,104
I would've dealt with him on my own.

623
00:47:56,937 --> 00:47:58,354
You were testing me. Okay.

624
00:47:58,437 --> 00:48:01,021
Let's put everyone to the test,
back to square one.

625
00:48:01,104 --> 00:48:05,562
Everybody's a blank slate,
and right now, Annabelle is going, period.

626
00:48:09,687 --> 00:48:12,271
Do what needs to be done. Don't fuck up.

627
00:48:30,854 --> 00:48:33,854
[introspective rap music playing]

628
00:48:43,146 --> 00:48:46,146
[rap music continues]

629
00:48:55,812 --> 00:48:58,396
[Ambre rapping on phone]

630
00:48:58,479 --> 00:49:01,479
- [Ambre rapping]
- [introspective rap music continues]

631
00:49:23,062 --> 00:49:25,729
- [rap music continues]
- [fire crackling]

632
00:49:30,312 --> 00:49:31,396
Everyone out!

633
00:49:31,479 --> 00:49:32,646
There's smoke, let's go!

634
00:49:32,729 --> 00:49:33,854
Move, go, go!

635
00:49:34,354 --> 00:49:35,937
Let's go, hurry up.

636
00:49:37,396 --> 00:49:40,437
Léo! Where's Léo? Where is he?

637
00:49:40,521 --> 00:49:42,562
It's okay, he's at soccer. Let's go.

638
00:49:43,062 --> 00:49:45,396
Go, run, run! You sure?

639
00:49:45,479 --> 00:49:46,604
[Cassandra] Yes.

640
00:49:52,687 --> 00:49:55,687
Léo! Léo, are you there?

641
00:49:56,187 --> 00:49:58,104
[muffled] God damn it!

642
00:49:58,187 --> 00:50:01,187
[rap music continues]

643
00:50:22,979 --> 00:50:25,979
["No time" by J-One playing]
